{
  "stem": "14060.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the old part of the city and the synagogue, where it was even further than that, was not near to us.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it came to the question of kosher bread.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, being Orthodox, this was important.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember that it was organized-- I mean, my grandfather, the farmer, so we had a tremendous larder and stocks of things-- that the bread was being prepared at home.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had a domestic.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had a manservant who did the more harder work.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But whenever it was ready, the dough, then the girl or the man took it over to the bakery was around-- a non-Jewish bakery around the corner.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, according to Jewish law, all you had to do is to put a piece of wood in, and then all the baking was kosher.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This is basically the-- the groundwork why Jewish bread can be baked in a non-Jewish bakery.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, no tins were used.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was an open-fire bakery, so from kashrut point of view, that wasn't interesting.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Something else, which-- basically, just for the way of life it was.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You know, cholent, people like it and do it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We didn't have, by the way, any gefilte fish.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It didn't exist, because we had plenty of carp and good various fishes.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So this, I presume, must have originated from areas where they had no fish or had no money to buy fish and they chopped up whatever bits of herring and whatnot so they created some sort of a mixture.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And really it was only after the war when I left from there that I first seen gefilte fish, strange as it may sound.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But the process of schooling verse a Shabbat, just that I can explain it to you.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Friday night was the normal proceeding.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
